# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv and micro-projects.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or even
#   fail to install all dependencies.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, pdm.lock is generally recommended to be committed.
#pdm.lock
#   pdm build stage
.pdm-build/

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/lincolnloop/layman and pdm
